SIMPLE: preface
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preface
<hw>Pref"ace</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧face</ets>; cf. Sp. <ets>prefacio</ets>,
<ets>prefacion</ets>, It. <ets>prefazio</ets>, <ets>prefazione</ets>;
all fr. L. <ets>praefatio</ets>, fr. <ets>praefari</ets> to speak or say
beforehand; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>fari</ets>, <ets>fatus</ets>,
to speak. See <er>Fate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something spoken as
introductory to a discourse, or written as introductory to a book or
essay; a proem; an introduction, or series of preliminary
remarks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This superficial tale⟦br⟧
Is but a <qex>preface</qex> of her worthy praise.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heaven's high behest no <qex>preface</qex> needs.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>The prelude or introduction
to the canon of the Mass.</def> <rj><au>Addis & Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Proper preface</b></col> <fld>(Ch. of Eng. & Prot. Epis.
Ch.)</fld>, <cd>a portion of the communion service, preceding the prayer
of consecration, appointed for certain seasons.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Introduction; preliminary; preamble; proem;
prelude; prologue.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preface</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Preface
<hw>Pref"ace</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Prefaced</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prefacing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To introduce by a preface; to
give a preface to; <as>as, to <ex>preface</ex> a book
discourse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preface</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Preface
<hw>Pref"ace</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a preface.</def>
<rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prefacer</ent>⟦br⟧
